Key Match Events: Vincent Aboubakar scored the winning goal in the 64th minute
Pre-Game Insights: The match was overshadowed by administrative disagreements between the Cameroon Football Federation and the Ministry of Sports and Physical Education
Post-Match Reflections: The victory was a symbol of unity for Cameroonians and a reminder to the feuding authorities to focus on supporting the team
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch conditions were poor, hindering both teams' natural style of play
Others: The Indomitable Lions are preparing to travel to Kampala for their second qualifying match against Zimbabwe on September 10
